#. type: Content of: <sections><section><title>
#: en/handbook/2006.1/hb-install-ppc-medium.xml:85
#, no-wrap
msgid "The Gentoo Universal Installation CD"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <sections><section><subsection><body><p>
#: en/handbook/2006.1/hb-install-ppc-medium.xml:91
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"Gentoo Linux can be installed using a <e>stage3</e> tarball file.\n"
"Such a tarball is an archive that contains a minimal environment from\n"
"which you can succesfully install Gentoo Linux onto your system.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <sections><section><subsection><body><p>
#: en/handbook/2006.1/hb-install-ppc-medium.xml:97
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"Installations using a stage1 or stage2 tarball file are not documented in the\n"
"Gentoo Handbook - please read the <uri link=\"/doc/en/faq.xml#stage12\">Gentoo\n"
"FAQ</uri> on these matters.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <sections><section><subsection><title>
#: en/handbook/2006.1/hb-install-ppc-medium.xml:105
#, no-wrap
msgid "Gentoo Universal Installation CD"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <sections><section><subsection><body><p>
#: en/handbook/2006.1/hb-install-ppc-medium.xml:109
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"An Installation CD is a bootable medium which contains a self-sustained Gentoo \n"
"environment. It allows you to boot Linux from the CD. During the boot process \n"
"your hardware is detected and the appropriate drivers are loaded. The Gentoo \n"
"Installation CDs are maintained by Gentoo developers.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <sections><section><subsection><body><p>
#: en/handbook/2006.1/hb-install-ppc-medium.xml:116
#, no-wrap
msgid "There currently are two Installation CDs available:\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <sections><section><subsection><body><ul><li>
#: en/handbook/2006.1/hb-install-ppc-medium.xml:121
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"    The Universal Installation CD contains everything you need to install \n"
"    Gentoo. It provides stage3 files for common architectures, source code \n"
"    for the extra applications you need to choose from and, of course, the \n"
"    installation instructions for your architecture.\n"
"  "
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <sections><section><subsection><body><ul><li>
#: en/handbook/2006.1/hb-install-ppc-medium.xml:127
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"    The Minimal Installation CD contains only a minimal environment that allows \n"
"    you to boot up and configure your network so you can connect to the \n"
"    Internet. It does not contain any additional files and cannot be used \n"
"    during the current installation approach.\n"
"  "
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <sections><section><subsection><body><p>
#: en/handbook/2006.1/hb-install-ppc-medium.xml:135
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"Gentoo also provides a Package CD. This is not an Installation CD but an\n"
"additional resource that you can exploit during the installation of your Gentoo\n"
"system. It contains prebuilt packages (also known as the GRP set) that allow\n"
"you to easily and quickly install additional applications (such as\n"
"OpenOffice.org, KDE, GNOME, ...) immediately after the Gentoo installation and\n"
"right before you update your Portage tree.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <sections><section><subsection><body><p>
#: en/handbook/2006.1/hb-install-ppc-medium.xml:144
#, no-wrap
msgid "The use of the Package CD is covered later in this document. \n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <sections><section><title>
#: en/handbook/2006.1/hb-install-ppc-medium.xml:152
#, no-wrap
msgid "Download, Burn and Boot the Gentoo Universal Installation CD"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <sections><section><subsection><title>
#: en/handbook/2006.1/hb-install-ppc-medium.xml:154
#, no-wrap
msgid "Downloading and Burning the Installation CD"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <sections><section><subsection><body><p>
#: en/handbook/2006.1/hb-install-ppc-medium.xml:158
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"You can download the Universal Installation CD (and, if you want to, the \n"
"Packages CD as well) from one of our <uri \n"
"link=\"/main/en/mirrors.xml\">mirrors</uri>. The Installation CDs are located \n"
"in the <path>releases/ppc/2006.1/ppc32/installcd</path> directory;\n"
"the Package CDs are located in the \n"
"<path>releases/ppc/2006.1/ppc32/packagecd</path> directory.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <sections><section><subsection><body><p>
#: en/handbook/2006.1/hb-install-ppc-medium.xml:167
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"Inside those directories you'll find ISO-files. Those are full CD images which\n"
"you can write on a CD-R.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <sections><section><subsection><body><p>
#: en/handbook/2006.1/hb-install-ppc-medium.xml:172
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"After downloading the file, you can verify its integrity to see if it is \n"
"corrupted or not:\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <sections><section><subsection><body><ul><li>
#: en/handbook/2006.1/hb-install-ppc-medium.xml:178
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"    You can check its MD5 checksum and compare it with the MD5 checksum we \n"
"    provide (for instance with the <c>md5sum</c> tool under Linux/Unix or \n"
"    <uri link=\"http://www.etree.org/md5com.html\">md5sum</uri> for Windows).\n"
"    Verifying MD5 checksums with Mac OS X is described in the <uri\n"
"    link=\"/doc/en/gentoo-ppc-faq.xml#doc_chap1\">Gentoo PPC FAQ</uri>.\n"
"  "
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <sections><section><subsection><body><ul><li>
#: en/handbook/2006.1/hb-install-ppc-medium.xml:185
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"    You can verify the cryptographic signature that we provide. You need to\n"
"    obtain the public key we use (0x17072058) before you proceed though.\n"
"  "
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <sections><section><subsection><body><p>
#: en/handbook/2006.1/hb-install-ppc-medium.xml:191
#, no-wrap
msgid "To fetch our public key using the GnuPG application, run the following command:\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Attribute 'caption' of: <sections><section><subsection><body><pre>
#: en/handbook/2006.1/hb-install-ppc-medium.xml:194
#, no-wrap
msgid "Obtaining the public key"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <sections><section><subsection><body><pre>
#: en/handbook/2006.1/hb-install-ppc-medium.xml:195
#, no-wrap
msgid "$ <i>gpg --keyserver subkeys.pgp.net --recv-keys 0x17072058</i>\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <sections><section><subsection><body><p>
#: en/handbook/2006.1/hb-install-ppc-medium.xml:199
#, no-wrap
msgid "Now verify the signature:\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Attribute 'caption' of: <sections><section><subsection><body><pre>
#: en/handbook/2006.1/hb-install-ppc-medium.xml:202
#, no-wrap
msgid "Verify the cryptographic signature"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <sections><section><subsection><body><pre>
#: en/handbook/2006.1/hb-install-ppc-medium.xml:203
#, no-wrap
msgid "$ <i>gpg --verify &lt;signature file&gt; &lt;downloaded iso&gt;</i>\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <sections><section><subsection><body><p>
#: en/handbook/2006.1/hb-install-ppc-medium.xml:207
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"To burn the downloaded ISO(s), you have to select raw-burning. How you\n"
"do this is highly program-dependent. We will discuss <c>cdrecord</c> and\n"
"<c>K3B</c> here; more information can be found in our <uri\n"
"link=\"/doc/en/faq.xml#isoburning\">Gentoo FAQ</uri>.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <sections><section><subsection><body><ul><li>
#: en/handbook/2006.1/hb-install-ppc-medium.xml:215
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"    With cdrecord, you simply type <c>cdrecord dev=/dev/hdc &lt;downloaded iso\n"
"    file&gt;</c> (replace <path>/dev/hdc</path> with your CD-RW drive's device\n"
"    path).\n"
"  "
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <sections><section><subsection><body><ul><li>
#: en/handbook/2006.1/hb-install-ppc-medium.xml:220
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"    With K3B, select <c>Tools</c> &gt; <c>CD</c> &gt; <c>Burn Image</c>. Then\n"
"    you can locate your ISO file within the 'Image to Burn' area. Finally click\n"
"    <c>Start</c>.\n"
"  "
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <sections><section><subsection><title>
#: en/handbook/2006.1/hb-install-ppc-medium.xml:229
#, no-wrap
msgid "Default: Booting the Installation CD with Yaboot"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <sections><section><subsection><body><p>
#: en/handbook/2006.1/hb-install-ppc-medium.xml:233
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"On NewWorld machines place the Installation CD in the CD-ROM and reboot the \n"
"system. When the system-start-bell sounds, simply hold down the 'C' until the\n"
"CD loads.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <sections><section><subsection><body><p>
#: en/handbook/2006.1/hb-install-ppc-medium.xml:239
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"After the Installation CD loaded, you will be greeted by a friendly welcome \n"
"message and a <e>boot:</e> prompt at the bottom of the screen.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <sections><section><subsection><body><p>
#: en/handbook/2006.1/hb-install-ppc-medium.xml:244
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"We provide one generic kernel, <e>apple</e>. This kernel is built with support\n"
"for multiple CPUs, but it will boot on single processor machines as well.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <sections><section><subsection><body><p>
#: en/handbook/2006.1/hb-install-ppc-medium.xml:249
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"You can tweak some kernel options at this prompt. The following table lists \n"
"some of the available boot options you can add:\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <sections><section><subsection><body><table><tr><th>
#: en/handbook/2006.1/hb-install-ppc-medium.xml:255
#, no-wrap
msgid "Boot Option"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <sections><section><subsection><body><table><tr><th>
#: en/handbook/2006.1/hb-install-ppc-medium.xml:256
#, no-wrap
msgid "Description"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <sections><section><subsection><body><table><tr><ti>
#: en/handbook/2006.1/hb-install-ppc-medium.xml:259
#, no-wrap
msgid "<c>video</c>"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <sections><section><subsection><body><table><tr><ti>
#: en/handbook/2006.1/hb-install-ppc-medium.xml:261
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"    This option takes one of the following vendor-specific tags:\n"
"    <c>nvidiafb</c>, <c>radeonfb</c>, <c>rivafb</c>, <c>atyfb</c>, \n"
"    <c>aty128</c> or <c>ofonly</c>. You can follow this tag with the resolution \n"
"    refresh rate and color depth you want to use. For instance,\n"
"    <c>video=radeonfb:1280x1024@75-32</c> will select the ATI Radeon frame buffer\n"
"    at a resolution of 1280x1024 with a refresh rate of 75Hz and a color depth of\n"
"    32 bits. If you are uncertain what to choose, and the default doesn't work,\n"
"    <c>video=ofonly</c> will most certainly work.\n"
"  "
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <sections><section><subsection><body><table><tr><ti>
#: en/handbook/2006.1/hb-install-ppc-medium.xml:272
#, no-wrap
msgid "<c>nol3</c>"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <sections><section><subsection><body><table><tr><ti>
#: en/handbook/2006.1/hb-install-ppc-medium.xml:274
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"    Disables level 3 cache on some PowerBooks (needed for at least the 17&quot;)\n"
"  "
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <sections><section><subsection><body><table><tr><ti>
#: en/handbook/2006.1/hb-install-ppc-medium.xml:278
#, no-wrap
msgid "<c>dofirewire</c>"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <sections><section><subsection><body><table><tr><ti>
#: en/handbook/2006.1/hb-install-ppc-medium.xml:280
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"    Enables support for IEEE1394 (FireWire) devices, like external harddisks.\n"
"  "
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <sections><section><subsection><body><table><tr><ti>
#: en/handbook/2006.1/hb-install-ppc-medium.xml:284
#, no-wrap
msgid "<c>dopcmcia</c>"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <sections><section><subsection><body><table><tr><ti>
#: en/handbook/2006.1/hb-install-ppc-medium.xml:286
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"    If you want to use PCMCIA devices during your installation (like PCMCIA\n"
"    network cards) you have to enable this option.\n"
"  "
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <sections><section><subsection><body><p>
#: en/handbook/2006.1/hb-install-ppc-medium.xml:293
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"To use the above options, at the <e>boot:</e> prompt, type <e>apple</e> followed\n"
"by the desired option.  In the example below, we'll force the kernel to use the\n"
"OpenFirmware framebuffer instead of the device specific driver.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Attribute 'caption' of: <sections><section><subsection><body><pre>
#: en/handbook/2006.1/hb-install-ppc-medium.xml:298
#, no-wrap
msgid "Force the use of the OpenFirmware framebuffer"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <sections><section><subsection><body><pre>
#: en/handbook/2006.1/hb-install-ppc-medium.xml:299
#, no-wrap
msgid "boot: <i>apple video=ofonly</i>\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <sections><section><subsection><body><p>
#: en/handbook/2006.1/hb-install-ppc-medium.xml:303
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"If you don't need to add any options, just hit enter at this prompt, and a \n"
"complete Gentoo Linux environment will be loaded from the CD. Continue with\n"
"<uri link=\"#booted\">And When You're Booted...</uri>.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <sections><section><subsection><title>
#: en/handbook/2006.1/hb-install-ppc-medium.xml:311
#, no-wrap
msgid "Alternative: Booting the Installation CD on a Pegasos"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <sections><section><subsection><body><p>
#: en/handbook/2006.1/hb-install-ppc-medium.xml:315
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"On the Pegasos simply insert the CD and at the SmartFirmware boot-prompt type\n"
"<c>boot cd /boot/menu</c>. This will open a small bootmenu where you can choose\n"
"between several preconfigured video configs. If you need any special boot\n"
"options you can append them to the command-line just like with Yaboot above. \n"
"For example: <c>boot cd /boot/pegasos video=radeonfb:1280x1024@75 mem=256M</c>.\n"
"The default kernel options (in case something goes wrong and you need it) are \n"
"preconfigured with <c>console=ttyS0,115200 console=tty0 init=/linuxrc \n"
"looptype=squashfs loop=/image.squashfs cdroot root=/dev/ram0</c>.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <sections><section><subsection><title>
#: en/handbook/2006.1/hb-install-ppc-medium.xml:329
#, no-wrap
msgid "Alternative: Booting the Installation CD with BootX"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <sections><section><subsection><body><p>
#: en/handbook/2006.1/hb-install-ppc-medium.xml:333
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"If you have an OldWorld Mac the bootable portion of the livecd can't be used.\n"
"The most simple solution is to use MacOS 9 or earlier to bootstrap into a Linux\n"
"environment with a tool called BootX.  \n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <sections><section><subsection><body><p>
#: en/handbook/2006.1/hb-install-ppc-medium.xml:339
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"First, download <uri link=\"http://penguinppc.org/projects/bootx/\">BootX</uri>\n"
"and unpack the archive.  Copy the the <c>BootX Extension</c> from the unpacked\n"
"archive into <c>Extensions Folder</c> and the BootX App Control Panel into\n"
"<c>Control Panels</c>, both of which are located in your MacOS System Folder.\n"
"Next, create a folder called \"Linux Kernels\" in your System folder and copy the\n"
"<c>apple</c> kernel from the CD to this folder.  Finally, copy <c>apple.igz</c> \n"
"from the Installation CD <path>boot</path> folder into the MacOS \n"
"<c>System Folder</c>.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <sections><section><subsection><body><p>
#: en/handbook/2006.1/hb-install-ppc-medium.xml:350
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"To prepare BootX, start the BootX App Control Panel.  First select the Options\n"
"dialog and check <c>Use Specified RAM Disk</c> and select <c>apple.igz</c> from\n"
"your System Folder.  Continue back to the initial screen and ensure that the\n"
"ramdisk size is at least <c>32000</c>.  Finally, set the kernel arguments as\n"
"shown below:\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Attribute 'caption' of: <sections><section><subsection><body><pre>
#: en/handbook/2006.1/hb-install-ppc-medium.xml:357
#, no-wrap
msgid "BootX kernel arguments"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <sections><section><subsection><body><pre>
#: en/handbook/2006.1/hb-install-ppc-medium.xml:358
#, no-wrap
msgid "cdroot root=/dev/ram0 init=linuxrc loop=image.squashfs looptype=squashfs console=tty0 \n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <sections><section><subsection><body><note>
#: en/handbook/2006.1/hb-install-ppc-medium.xml:362
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"The kernel parameters in the yaboot section above are also applicable here. You\n"
"can append any of those options to the kernel arguments above.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <sections><section><subsection><body><p>
#: en/handbook/2006.1/hb-install-ppc-medium.xml:367
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"Check once more to make sure the settings are correct and then save the \n"
"configuration.  This saves typing just in case it doesn't boot or something is\n"
"missing.  Press the Linux button at the top of the window.  If everything goes\n"
"correctly, it should boot into the Installation CD. Continue with \n"
"<uri link=\"#booted\">And When You're Booted...</uri>\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <sections><section><subsection><title>
#: en/handbook/2006.1/hb-install-ppc-medium.xml:378
#, no-wrap
msgid "And When You're Booted..."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <sections><section><subsection><body><p>
#: en/handbook/2006.1/hb-install-ppc-medium.xml:382
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"You will be greeted by a root (\"#\") prompt on the current console. You can also \n"
"switch to other consoles by pressing Alt-F2, Alt-F3 and Alt-F4. Get \n"
"back to the one you started on by pressing Alt-F1.  Due to the keyboard layout,\n"
"you may need to press Alt-fn-Fx on Apple machines.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <sections><section><subsection><body><p>
#: en/handbook/2006.1/hb-install-ppc-medium.xml:389
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"If you are installing Gentoo on a system with a non-US keyboard, use\n"
"<c>loadkeys</c> to load the keymap for your keyboard. To list the available\n"
"keymaps, execute <c>ls /usr/share/keymaps/i386</c>.  On NewWorld machines or the\n"
"Pegasos do not use the keymaps in <path>ppc</path> or <path>mac</path> as they\n"
"are for ADB-based OldWorld machines.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Attribute 'caption' of: <sections><section><subsection><body><pre>
#: en/handbook/2006.1/hb-install-ppc-medium.xml:396
#, no-wrap
msgid "Listing available keymaps"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <sections><section><subsection><body><pre>
#: en/handbook/2006.1/hb-install-ppc-medium.xml:397
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"<comment>(PPC uses x86 keymaps on most systems. The mac/ppc keymaps provided\n"
" on the Installation CD are ADB keymaps and unusable with the Installation CD \n"
" kernel)</comment>\n"
"# <i>ls /usr/share/keymaps/i386</i>\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <sections><section><subsection><body><p>
#: en/handbook/2006.1/hb-install-ppc-medium.xml:404
#, no-wrap
msgid "Now load the keymap of your choice:\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Attribute 'caption' of: <sections><section><subsection><body><pre>
#: en/handbook/2006.1/hb-install-ppc-medium.xml:407
#, no-wrap
msgid "Loading a keymap"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <sections><section><subsection><body><pre>
#: en/handbook/2006.1/hb-install-ppc-medium.xml:408
#, no-wrap
msgid "# <i>loadkeys be-latin1</i>\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <sections><section><subsection><body><p>
#: en/handbook/2006.1/hb-install-ppc-medium.xml:412
#, no-wrap
msgid "Now continue with <uri link=\"#hardware\">Extra Hardware Configuration</uri>.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <sections><section><subsection><title>
#: en/handbook/2006.1/hb-install-ppc-medium.xml:418
#, no-wrap
msgid "Extra Hardware Configuration"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <sections><section><subsection><body><p>
#: en/handbook/2006.1/hb-install-ppc-medium.xml:422
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"When the Installation CD boots, it tries to detect all your hardware devices and\n"
"loads the appropriate kernel modules to support your hardware. In the\n"
"vast majority of cases, it does a very good job. However, in some cases, it may\n"
"not auto-load the kernel modules you need. If the PCI auto-detection missed some\n"
"of your system's hardware, you will have to load the appropriate kernel modules\n"
"manually. \n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <sections><section><subsection><body><p>
#: en/handbook/2006.1/hb-install-ppc-medium.xml:431
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"In the next example we try to load the <c>airport</c> module.  This module\n"
"supports only the old Airport cards (802.11b).  Airport Extreme (802.11g) is not\n"
"supported on the InstallCD due to restrictions on firmware distribution.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Attribute 'caption' of: <sections><section><subsection><body><pre>
#: en/handbook/2006.1/hb-install-ppc-medium.xml:436
#, no-wrap
msgid "Loading the airport module"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <sections><section><subsection><body><pre>
#: en/handbook/2006.1/hb-install-ppc-medium.xml:437
#, no-wrap
msgid "# <i>modprobe airport</i>\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <sections><section><subsection><body><p>
#: en/handbook/2006.1/hb-install-ppc-medium.xml:441
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"On older iMacs, sometimes the network card is not detected properly.  These use\n"
"the BMAC driver:\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Attribute 'caption' of: <sections><section><subsection><body><pre>
#: en/handbook/2006.1/hb-install-ppc-medium.xml:445
#, no-wrap
msgid "Loading the bmac module"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <sections><section><subsection><body><pre>
#: en/handbook/2006.1/hb-install-ppc-medium.xml:446
#, no-wrap
msgid "# <i>modprobe bmac</i>\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <sections><section><subsection><title>
#: en/handbook/2006.1/hb-install-ppc-medium.xml:452
#, no-wrap
msgid "Optional: Tweaking Hard Disk Performance"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <sections><section><subsection><body><p>
#: en/handbook/2006.1/hb-install-ppc-medium.xml:456
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"If you are an advanced user, you might want to tweak the IDE hard disk\n"
"performance using <c>hdparm</c>. With the <c>-tT</c> options you can\n"
"test the performance of your disk (execute it several times to get a\n"
"more precise impression):\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Attribute 'caption' of: <sections><section><subsection><body><pre>
#: en/handbook/2006.1/hb-install-ppc-medium.xml:462
#, no-wrap
msgid "Testing disk performance"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <sections><section><subsection><body><pre>
#: en/handbook/2006.1/hb-install-ppc-medium.xml:463
#, no-wrap
msgid "# <i>hdparm -tT /dev/hda</i>\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <sections><section><subsection><body><p>
#: en/handbook/2006.1/hb-install-ppc-medium.xml:467
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"To tweak, you can use any of the following examples (or experiment\n"
"yourself) which use <path>/dev/hda</path> as disk (substitute with your\n"
"disk):\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Attribute 'caption' of: <sections><section><subsection><body><pre>
#: en/handbook/2006.1/hb-install-ppc-medium.xml:472
#, no-wrap
msgid "Tweaking hard disk performance"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <sections><section><subsection><body><pre>
#: en/handbook/2006.1/hb-install-ppc-medium.xml:473
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"<comment>Activate DMA:</comment>                                       # <i>hdparm -d 1 /dev/hda</i>\n"
"<comment>Activate DMA + Safe Performance-enhancing Options:</comment>  # <i>hdparm -d 1 -A 1 -m 16 -u 1 -a 64 /dev/hda</i>\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <sections><section><subsection><title>
#: en/handbook/2006.1/hb-install-ppc-medium.xml:480
#, no-wrap
msgid "Optional: User Accounts"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <sections><section><subsection><body><p>
#: en/handbook/2006.1/hb-install-ppc-medium.xml:484
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"If you plan on giving other people access to your installation\n"
"environment or you want to chat using <c>irssi</c> without root privileges (for\n"
"security reasons), you need to create the necessary user accounts and change \n"
"the root password.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <sections><section><subsection><body><p>
#: en/handbook/2006.1/hb-install-ppc-medium.xml:491
#, no-wrap
msgid "To change the root password, use the <c>passwd</c> utility:\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Attribute 'caption' of: <sections><section><subsection><body><pre>
#: en/handbook/2006.1/hb-install-ppc-medium.xml:494
#, no-wrap
msgid "Changing the root password"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <sections><section><subsection><body><pre>
#: en/handbook/2006.1/hb-install-ppc-medium.xml:495
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"# <i>passwd</i>\n"
"New password: <comment>(Enter your new password)</comment>\n"
"Re-enter password: <comment>(Re-enter your password)</comment>\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <sections><section><subsection><body><p>
#: en/handbook/2006.1/hb-install-ppc-medium.xml:501
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"To create a user account, we first enter their credentials, followed by\n"
"its password. We use <c>useradd</c> and <c>passwd</c> for these tasks.\n"
"In the next example, we create a user called &quot;john&quot;.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Attribute 'caption' of: <sections><section><subsection><body><pre>
#: en/handbook/2006.1/hb-install-ppc-medium.xml:506
#, no-wrap
msgid "Creating a user account"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <sections><section><subsection><body><pre>
#: en/handbook/2006.1/hb-install-ppc-medium.xml:507
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"# <i>useradd -m -G users john</i>\n"
"# <i>passwd john</i>\n"
"New password: <comment>(Enter john's password)</comment>\n"
"Re-enter password: <comment>(Re-enter john's password)</comment>\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <sections><section><subsection><body><p>
#: en/handbook/2006.1/hb-install-ppc-medium.xml:514
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"You can change your user id from root to the newly created user by using\n"
"<c>su</c>:\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Attribute 'caption' of: <sections><section><subsection><body><pre>
#: en/handbook/2006.1/hb-install-ppc-medium.xml:518
#, no-wrap
msgid "Changing user id"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <sections><section><subsection><body><pre>
#: en/handbook/2006.1/hb-install-ppc-medium.xml:519
#, no-wrap
msgid "# <i>su - john</i>\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <sections><section><subsection><title>
#: en/handbook/2006.1/hb-install-ppc-medium.xml:525
#, no-wrap
msgid "Optional: Viewing Documentation while Installing"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <sections><section><subsection><body><p>
#: en/handbook/2006.1/hb-install-ppc-medium.xml:529
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"If you want to view the Gentoo Handbook (either from-CD or online) during the\n"
"installation, make sure you have created a user account (see <uri\n"
"link=\"#useraccounts\">Optional: User Accounts</uri>). Then press <c>Alt-F2</c> to\n"
"go to a new terminal and log in.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <sections><section><subsection><body><p>
#: en/handbook/2006.1/hb-install-ppc-medium.xml:536
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"If you want to view the documentation on the CD you can immediately run\n"
"<c>links</c> or even <c>links -g</c> for a graphical framebuffer browser to\n"
"read it:\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Attribute 'caption' of: <sections><section><subsection><body><pre>
#: en/handbook/2006.1/hb-install-ppc-medium.xml:541
#, no-wrap
msgid "Viewing the on-CD documentation"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <sections><section><subsection><body><pre>
#: en/handbook/2006.1/hb-install-ppc-medium.xml:542
#, no-wrap
msgid "# <i>links /mnt/cdrom/docs/html/index.html</i>\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <sections><section><subsection><body><p>
#: en/handbook/2006.1/hb-install-ppc-medium.xml:546
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"However, it is preferred that you use the online Gentoo Handbook as it will be\n"
"more recent than the one provided on the CD. You can view it using <c>links</c>\n"
"as well, but only after having completed the <e>Configuring your Network</e>\n"
"chapter (otherwise you won't be able to go on the Internet to view the\n"
"document):\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Attribute 'caption' of: <sections><section><subsection><body><pre>
#: en/handbook/2006.1/hb-install-ppc-medium.xml:553
#, no-wrap
msgid "Viewing the Online Documentation"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <sections><section><subsection><body><pre>
#: en/handbook/2006.1/hb-install-ppc-medium.xml:554
#, no-wrap
msgid "# <i>links http://www.gentoo.org/doc/en/handbook/handbook-ppc.xml</i>\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <sections><section><subsection><body><p>
#: en/handbook/2006.1/hb-install-ppc-medium.xml:558
#, no-wrap
msgid "You can go back to your original terminal by pressing <c>Alt-F1</c>.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <sections><section><subsection><title>
#: en/handbook/2006.1/hb-install-ppc-medium.xml:564
#, no-wrap
msgid "Optional: Starting the SSH Daemon"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <sections><section><subsection><body><p>
#: en/handbook/2006.1/hb-install-ppc-medium.xml:568
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"If you want to allow other users to access your computer during the\n"
"Gentoo installation (perhaps because those users are going to help you\n"
"install Gentoo, or even do it for you), you need to create a user\n"
"account for them and perhaps even provide them with your root password \n"
"(<e>only</e> do that <e>if</e> you <b>fully trust</b> that user).\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <sections><section><subsection><body><p>
#: en/handbook/2006.1/hb-install-ppc-medium.xml:576
#, no-wrap
msgid "To fire up the SSH daemon, execute the following command:\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Attribute 'caption' of: <sections><section><subsection><body><pre>
#: en/handbook/2006.1/hb-install-ppc-medium.xml:579
#, no-wrap
msgid "Starting the SSH daemon"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <sections><section><subsection><body><pre>
#: en/handbook/2006.1/hb-install-ppc-medium.xml:580
#, no-wrap
msgid "# <i>/etc/init.d/sshd start</i>\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <sections><section><subsection><body><p>
#: en/handbook/2006.1/hb-install-ppc-medium.xml:584
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"To be able to use sshd, you first need to set up your networking. Continue with\n"
"the chapter on <uri link=\"?part=1&amp;chap=3\">Configuring your Network</uri>.\n"
msgstr ""
